   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>So, we'd seen this happen with Triskelios (I believe). We tried to duplicate it 
consistently but failed. It just happened to me so I thought I'd note the path for 
someone else. It's really fun :)

Attached is screenshot of the oddness on Windows 7 Chrome.

1. Go to your edit profile page: <a href="http://openhatch.org/profile/views/edit_info">http://openhatch.org/profile/views/edit_info</a> . I 
added some to the "I understand:" field.
2. Click save.
3. Click "home" (upper left of nav to take you to logged-in user home/landing page)
4. Bugs should be taking a while to load/recalculate. The page is probably looking 
a little like the attached screenshot.
5. If you hit reload, things will go back to rightness.

Was able to reproduce this on Firefox 3.6.17 on Win 7 as well.</pre>
   </td>
